  "text": "We will now make another crucial observation, which will give more information about the fibers of the standard submersion. Since by Lemma 3.6 every fiber F of the standard submersion is totally geodesic, the Levi-Civita connection of M restricts to the Levi-Civita connection of F , and the connection ∇ τ restricts to a connection ∇ F with parallel, skewsymmetric torsion T F := 2τ v | F . Proof. In order to keep the notation simple, we will identify here k-representations with the associated bundles over M, and notice that every k-invariant object corresponds to a ∇ τ -parallel section on M. Since so(v j ) ∩ k is trivial for each irreducible summand v j of v, [CITATION_1] Thm. 4.4] shows by immediate induction on the number of components v j that the space K(k) of algebraic curvature tensors with values in k satisfies",
